parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_CELL_MAXBITRATE_DL_DRB
parametertype.description: Maximum cell bit rate for the DL, measured during one sampling period. The sampling period can be the time between cell trace events, i.e. one complete cell trace period, a cell trace period interrupted by instant counter read out or the time inbetween multiple instant counter read outs. The measurement is based on periodic reports from a data provider where the max value is taken from the report with the highest bit rate value within the sampling period.
parametertype.comment: BbAdapter created

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_COLLECTED_CELL_CAPACITY_SAMPLES

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_COLLECTION_PERIODS
parametertype.description: Number of BbAdaptor collection periods included in event

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_COMMON_LENGTH
parametertype.description: Number of bytes in COMMON message

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_COMMON_MSG
parametertype.description: The message content has variable length. This parameter has a limit of 4 Kbytes according to 3GPP. The actual size used is variable as the recording functions only use the same amount of space as is required by the message so no wasted space will occur - i.e.even if the size is 4 Kbytes, this will only be fully used if the message contents are actually 4 Kbytes long.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_CONFIGVERSIONID
parametertype.description: Indicate the version of the MOM parameters stored.
parametertype.comment: Used by the PmController to determine if the received Local event INTRAFREQ1 shall be used for stepping the counters. The value of EVENT_PARAM_CONFIGVERSON shall be equal to the value stored in the PmController for that the counter shall be stepped.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_CONFLICTING_FLEX_FILTER_BITMAP
parametertype.description: Bitmap pointing out filter parameters not being applicable to the base flexible counter, EVENT_PARAM_FLEX_BASE_NAME. (LSB) Bit position 0=PLMN index, 1=UE Category, 2=SPID, 3=QCI, 4=ARP, 5=LCG, Other bits=reserved for future. The value of this parameter can be UNAVAILABLE when there is no PmFlexCounterFilter MO instance or all configured filter parameters are disabled.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_CONN_USERS_VIOLATION

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_CONTENTION_DETECTED

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_CAUSE

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_COVERAGE_CELL_ID
parametertype.description: Identity of the cell, defined in MOM. Same as EVENT_PARAM_GLOBAL_CELL_ID. When the wakeup was result from an activation request from a coverage cell, this is the eNB ID of the coverage cell. Otherwise, when the wakeup was triggered by the capacity cell itself due to time interval expiry or other fault conditions, this parameter is set to UNAVAILABLE.
parametertype.comment: pc1+. Global Cell ID

parametertype.name: EVENT_ARRAY_COVERAGE_CELL_ID

parametertype.comment: pc1+. Global Cell ID

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_DETECTION_DL_PRB_THRESHOLD
parametertype.description: The configured DL PRB usage percentage threshold for the cell sleep or wakeup detection. When the coverage cell successfully detect that the capacity cell need to be wakeup by exceeding threshold, the coverage cell set to right value. Otherwise, when the coverage cell detect by its abnormal state (e.g. overload) and the capacity cell detect for itself that it should be wakeup(e.g. X2 broken), this parameter is set to UNAVAILABLE.
parametertype.comment: pc1+

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_DETECTION_DL_PRB_USAGE
parametertype.description: The adjusted DL PRB usage percentage during the cell sleep or wakeup detection. When the coverage cell successfully detect that the capacity cell need to be wakeup by exceeding threshold, the coverage cell set to right value. Otherwise, when the coverage cell detect by its abnormal state (e.g. overload) and the capacity cell detect for itself that it should be wakeup(e.g. X2 broken), this parameter is set to UNAVAILABLE.
parametertype.comment: pc1+

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_DETECTION_DURATION
parametertype.description: The configured duration for the cell sleep or wakeup detection. When the coverage cell successfully detect that the capacity cell need to be wakeup by exceeding threshold, the coverage cell set to right value. Otherwise, when the coverage cell detect by its abnormal state (e.g. overload) and the capacity cell detect for itself that it should be wakeup(e.g. X2 broken), this parameter is set to UNAVAILABLE.
parametertype.comment: pc1+

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_DETECTION_UES
parametertype.description: The adjusted number of RRC connections found during the cell sleep or wakeup detection. When the coverage cell successfully detect that the capacity cell need to be wakeup by exceeding threshold, the coverage cell set to right value. Otherwise, when the coverage cell detect by its abnormal state (e.g. overload) and the capacity cell detect for itself that it should be wakeup(e.g. X2 broken), this parameter is set to UNAVAILABLE.
parametertype.comment: pc1+. No. of RRC connections

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_DETECTION_UES_THRESHOLD
parametertype.description: The configured number of RRC connections threshold for the cell sleep or wakeup detection. When the coverage cell successfully detect that the capacity cell need to be wakeup by exceeding threshold, the coverage cell set to right value. Otherwise, when the coverage cell detect by its abnormal state (e.g. overload) and the capacity cell detect for itself that it should be wakeup(e.g. X2 broken), this parameter is set to UNAVAILABLE.
parametertype.comment: pc1+. No. of RRC connections

The number of VoIP sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of NOT satisfactory quality in a cell. A VoIP session is considered of satisfactory quality if 99% of the total sent packets in uplink are received within the packet delay budget.

Number of VoIP users that are NOT considered satiesfied in a cell. A VoIP user is considered satiesfied if 99% of the total sentpackets in uplink are received within the packet delay budget.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_WIFI_THROUGHPUT_ESTIMATE_EUTRA_CONNECTED
parametertype.description: The weighted UE specific average throughput computed when a UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode requests access in a WiFi Cell. The value of this EUTRA throughput is used by the eNB together with the WiFi throughput received from the WiFi Access Controller to make a decision on whether to allow access for the UE in WiFi or not.

parametertype.name: EVENT_PARAM_WIFI_THROUGHPUT_ESTIMATE_WIFI
parametertype.description: The UE specific throughput in the WiFi cell where the UE is requesting access. The value of this WiFi throughput is used by the eNB together with the weighted average UE specific throughput estimated in the EUTRA cell to make a decision on whether to allow access for the UE in WiFi or not.
